Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.54,0:05:22.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:21.82,0:05:23.18,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:05:23.28,0:05:24.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:24.03,0:05:25.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Like I'm gonna!{guess}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:30.99,0:05:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri, let's hurry home.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:32.88,0:05:34.65,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened, brother?
Dialogue: 0,0:05:34.91,0:05:36.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The rain starts any minute.
Dialogue: 0,0:05:53.05,0:05:54.69,Default,,0,0,0,,You've done enough!
Dialogue: 0,0:05:54.69,0:05:56.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Go back inside!{Return to safety/house!}
Dialogue: 0,0:05:56.65,0:05:57.80,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:06:10.54,0:06:11.87,Default,,0,0,0,,It's alright!{Nothing to worry!}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:11.87,0:06:14.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad just needs to sell this lumber{/timber} in the city!{/is going to the city to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:14.58,0:06:16.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll finally have a dinner!{in the book, they used to starve a lot until dad returns with some wheat, so I think the meaning is this, though it sounds closer to "after this, let's go eat"}
Dialogue: 0,0:06:58.22,0:07:00.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother, what about school?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:00.75,0:07:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no one attends it anymore.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:02.46,0:07:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's as the teacher said. \NBecause of the famine{/hunger/shortage of crops}, everyone is in dismay.{osawagi is rather "clamour; clamor; uproar; tumult; furore; furor"}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:03.99,0:07:06.54,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:06.57,0:07:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of famine?
Dialogue: 0,0:07:08.63,0:07:11.74,Default,,0,0,0,,We're all in trouble as long as we can't harvest \Na single grain of rice{maybe use more specific "oryza"?}.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:12.66,0:07:16.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So we're not the only ones \Nhaving an empty stomach?{So we're not the only ones who can't get any dinner/rice/food?}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:16.03,0:07:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah. It's this way for everyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:17.92,0:07:23.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Even though dad is selling the trunks that big, he can only afford a handful of wheat flour.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:24.52,0:07:27.57,Default,,0,0,0,,But I have been hungry for so long...{/my belly is empty after all}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:29.74,0:07:31.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri, you can eat this.
Dialogue: 0,0:07:31.38,0:07:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not enough to have a fill, still...{/Even though it's not barely enough to get full./you can't fill your belly with that}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:37.29,0:07:41.82,Default,,0,0,0,,More than that — not just mushrooms or {konara }oak acorns{added because you can't eat oak}, \Nbut you can also even eat the wood bark!
Dialogue: 0,0:07:44.21,0:07:47.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Next time, take me along. \NI'll get my fill!{unsure, maybe "stuff my pockets with it" or smt}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:47.21,0:07:47.92,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:07:48.46,0:07:49.36,Default,,0,0,0,,I will.{/gonna do this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:07:49.36,0:07:51.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Really? Make sure you do!
Dialogue: 0,0:08:20.58,0:08:26.71,Default,,0,0,0,,{this is the original text and the lit translation for this lullaby, I tried my utmost to rhyme it: 一にゃこわいのは子守りコの役だね\N二にゃ憎まれ　\N三にゃ叫ばれでね\N四にゃ叱られ　\N五にゃ小言されでね\N六にゃろくなもの食べさせられでね\N七にゃしめしなんど洗わせられでね\N八にゃはだがれ　\N九にゃ口説がれでね\N十にゃ遠山さ歩がせられでね\N The first thing I'm afraid of is a nanny's role.\NSecond — being hated, third — being shout at.\NFourth — being scolded, fifth — being lectured. [end of section present in the movie]\NSixth — made to eat something inedible; seventh — made to do laundry; eighth — aging skin; ninth — quarreling with spouse; tenth — being sent into the mountains.}{\i1}~First thing of which I'm afraid \Nis a nanny's wretched fate~
