Dialogue: 0,0:08:43.77,0:08:45.10,Default,,0,0,0,,What is this sound?
Dialogue: 0,0:08:45.41,0:08:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Your father is getting the horse out to sell it!{/going to sell the horse}
Dialogue: 0,0:08:56.34,0:09:00.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Move it! Get out! Get out, you nag!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:00.79,0:09:02.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Stop it!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:03.11,0:09:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad! Don't do it! Don't sell{I'm at a complete loss for this word, rus translation just says "don't!" and I hear something like korona/kuroda but neither koro/kuro seem to be verbs applicable here to use "na" as to say "don't ...", maybe it's "dispose of/leave/part with" or just "beat"} her!
Dialogue: 0,0:09:58.59,0:10:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd better go play in the forest!{Lit: I'll go ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:31.74,0:10:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Does it bite?{Got something?}
Dialogue: 0,0:10:34.31,0:10:38.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Say, brother, \Nwhen is dad returning home?
Dialogue: 0,0:10:39.76,0:10:41.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Empty{it sounds like "ashita" which is tomorrow, but that makes no sense so I double the rus sub and suggest this, since this line is not particularly important: Probably tomorrow} again...
Dialogue: 0,0:10:42.88,0:10:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's go, Neri.
Dialogue: 0,0:10:45.31,0:10:47.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad may have already returned.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:26.35,0:11:29.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll go look for your dad.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:29.02,0:11:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You two stay here. \NAnd don't you think about going outside!
Dialogue: 0,0:11:32.75,0:11:37.22,Default,,0,0,0,,There's... There's flour in that cupboard. \NYou two eat it, but only a little.
Dialogue: 0,0:11:49.08,0:11:50.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Stay indoors!{/I told you to stay home}
Dialogue: 0,0:11:53.82,0:11:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,What a pair of unruly{/not listening to what I say/what disobedient} children I have here!
Dialogue: 0,0:12:38.54,0:12:42.07,Default,,0,0,0,,{I don't seem to find this murmur in the book and the rus sub makes it up, so might as well make something up too, or skip altogether}
Dialogue: 0,0:12:42.71,0:12:44.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri, let's eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:44.62,0:12:46.08,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:12:48.01,0:12:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on, Neri.
Dialogue: 0,0:12:52.48,0:12:53.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:02.40,0:13:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Mom!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:03.36,0:13:05.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Good evening. \NIs anyone home?
Dialogue: 0,0:13:06.51,0:13:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Dad!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:15.83,0:13:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been sent here{/come here} \Nto deliver this region from famine{/aid this region's hunger problem}.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:21.13,0:13:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, eat some.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:22.80,0:13:25.95,Default,,0,0,0,,Come on! You should eat.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:30.56,0:13:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You look like good children.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:32.60,0:13:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,But just being good children rotting in here \Nis besides the point.{/But what's the point of good children rotting in here?}{lit: just being ... means nothing/comes out into nothing}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:36.13,0:13:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You should leave{/come} with me.
Dialogue: 0,0:13:37.77,0:13:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The boy may look strong, \Nbut I can't keep you both.{After all, the boy looks strong, and I can't bring/take along two anyway./two can't accompany me}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:41.80,0:13:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, the girl one. If you stay here, \Nyou won't be getting anything more to eat.{Lit: there is already no food left}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:47.16,0:13:49.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Move{/go} to the city with daddy{/uncle}!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:49.16,0:13:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There, you won't ever feel short of bread.{/Over there, you will have daily bread.}{/will get full with bread every day}
Dialogue: 0,0:13:52.12,0:13:53.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:54.04,0:13:57.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Help me! Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:13:55.58,0:13:57.95,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:14:00.49,0:14:01.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:05.30,0:14:09.14,Default,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,1400)}Brother!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.52,0:14:23.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri!
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.65,0:14:29.30,Default,,0,0,0,,You finally woke up?{/Finally awake again?}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:29.30,0:14:32.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Planning to keep starving further on? \NHow light-headed.{You plan to just keep starving further on? \NVery light-headed of you.}{Lit "You still intend to famine" and I'm very unsure as to what it really stands for}{https://ja.hinative.com/questions/18888973}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:34.37,0:14:37.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri, dad, mom...
Dialogue: 0,0:14:37.37,0:14:38.97,Default,,0,0,0,,It's famine, after all{/all because of a famine}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:39.62,0:14:43.48,Default,,0,0,0,,We have the likes of you all over the place these days{/folks just like you are everywhere now}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:46.36,0:14:47.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, no use to overwork{/excert} yourself{murida is "doing something excessive/unreasonable/beyond one's powers"}.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:47.87,0:14:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You tripped over{/collapsed/were lying down} in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:49.78,0:14:53.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I went through trouble \Nto watch over you for 6 days straight!{he uses 3rd person construction, used in japanese to emphasize one's own importance}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:56.43,0:14:58.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep going! {/that's the way}
Dialogue: 0,0:14:58.60,0:15:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So I reckon, isn't it about time \Nyou return the favor? {/wouldn't it be nice of you to give something in return?}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.23,0:15:03.14,Default,,0,0,0,,But…
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.07,0:15:06.94,Default,,0,0,0,,This is... Neri's!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:10.57,0:15:13.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And this... is our house!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.46,0:15:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And a chimney?!{it's a weird way to say "we now have a chimney" and sounds rather like "up to the chimney" but I see no better explanations}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:22.78,0:15:33.43,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H080F27&\3c&H436A84&\blur1\bord0.2\pos(170,80)}Ihatovo \NSilk{tegusu is rather "wilk silk; silkworm gut; catgut" but I think that's way too complicated, we should leave it just "silk" because what does it matter for the specific details of a region's way for extracting it? also, 2012 movie translation used "silkworm gut" and that had me scratching my fucking head as to why it is called that} \NFactory
Dialogue: 1,0:15:24.09,0:15:26.17,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Ihatovo Silk Factory?{\i0}
Dialogue: 1,0:15:26.56,0:15:29.22,Default,,0,0,0,,No way! This is our house!
Dialogue: 1,0:15:29.71,0:15:33.43,Default,,0,0,0,,There ain't no house of yours anymore. \NOnly my silk factory.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:33.64,0:15:37.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Both this house and the forest \Naround this place — I bought everything!
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.43,0:15:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, don't droop,{/Well, it doesn't mean you should lose heart.}{/don't be discouraged} \NAfter all,{/like it or not} you can't alter the famine's ways{/it was all because of famine}.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:41.17,0:15:43.82,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:15:45.71,0:15:51.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, you still have to return the favor to me, \Nas to someone you owe your life to{/are greatly indebted to/your patron/benefactor}.{/this way you won't be able to return ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:53.21,0:15:57.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you believe you're above that,{/you hate this idea/you don't want it} \Nfeel free to get lost to the four winds!{it's rather "I want you to go wherever you wish"}
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.57,0:16:00.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Just keep in mind{/after all} — \Nthere won't be any food wherever you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:02.21,0:16:03.61,Default,,0,0,0,,In that case...
Dialogue: 0,0:16:04.13,0:16:06.60,Default,,0,0,0,,I see! Now we're talking!{/changed your mind}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.96,0:16:08.26,Default,,0,0,0,,I need your help hanging the nets.{網掛け is like "covering with #s"}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:08.26,0:16:11.09,Default,,0,0,0,,You will be hanging the nets \Non chestnut trees in the forest.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:11.09,0:16:13.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, we'll breed{/raise} silkworm with it!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.72,0:16:14.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Look there!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:17.26,0:16:19.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Do silkworms really breed there?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:19.33,0:16:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,They breed!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:20.92,0:16:22.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, don't bring bad luck,{/Hey, quit premonishing!}{engi may be both "ill-omen" and "put up an act", tho latter is unlikely}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:22.44,0:16:25.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would I set up{/found/build} a factory \Nin a place where silkworm can't breed?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:25.80,0:16:27.27,Default,,0,0,0,,It {\i1}must{\i0} breed well!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:27.27,0:16:31.40,Default,,0,0,0,,For your knowledge, it's not just me — \Na ton of other people already make living out of it!{Lit: starting from me, ... - 現におれをはじめたくさんのものが、それでくらしを立てているんだ - this line is in the book}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.40,0:16:34.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, you go there too, and get to work. \NTo work! Hurry!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:38.48,0:16:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,How limp{ふにゃふにゃ} can you really be?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:40.53,0:16:42.40,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure are one unbearable{/good for nothing - 仕様がない} fellow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:43.41,0:16:46.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Look, you can have this {steamed - 蒸しパン}bun, \Nbut you owe me even bigger one now!{/but you gotta bust your spine now}
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.96,0:16:48.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure is one unbearable fellow!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.85,0:16:54.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You there! \NMake sure to tighten{/fix/secure}{unsure} that one better!
Dialogue: 0,0:16:54.51,0:16:56.55,Default,,0,0,0,,This way, we won't have any silkworms!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:11.94,0:17:13.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You there! Hang it higher!{I can hardly hear a word here, but I hear "ro" which is imperative suffix}
Dialogue: 0,0:17:33.97,0:17:36.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Firewood!{薪} Start gathering firewood!
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.11,0:17:56.74,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fax0.05\fs15\pos(460,130)\bord0.2\blur1\c&H030C0E&\3c&H273232&\fry340}Ihatovo \NSilk \NFactory
Dialogue: 1,0:17:52.14,0:17:54.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori! What is taking you so long?{/for how much longer will you be dawdling there}
Dialogue: 0,0:18:29.17,0:18:32.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The hell!? What? Huh? What was that?
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.46,0:18:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:33.23,0:18:33.95,Default,,0,0,0,,The sky!...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:38.40,0:18:39.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It's coming{/getting closer/approaching; with a slight chance this might be "dark/darkens"}!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.87,0:18:42.85,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you mean? \NWhat is coming?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:43.23,0:18:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,What's going on?!
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.13,0:18:59.36,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be the volcano eruption.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:59.36,0:19:00.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It's over. 
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.38,0:19:03.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Damn it! \NMy silkworms are all done for{全滅}!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:22.97,0:20:25.45,Default,,0,0,0,,No way, no way! \NI tell you, no way this works!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:26.30,0:20:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever I suggest, \Nyou always dismiss me as a crank!{/Whatever I suggest, you always decide/have always decided to just disregard(it's stick/attach so I think here it's "stigmatize/stick a reputation" but I'm not sure) me as an adventurer!/nuts/speculator/charlatan}{なんでもかんでも、おれは山師張るときめた}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:29.89,0:20:31.85,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm just telling you to stop, so stop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.85,0:20:36.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative{/hell no}{it's his catchphrase "no" - unya}! My estimate is certain that this year will be as hot as the previous three together!{うんにゃ、おれの見込みでは、ことしは三年分暑いに相違ない}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:36.69,0:20:39.86,Default,,0,0,0,,In other words, \NI'll harvest three years' worth of crop!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.86,0:20:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Drop it, crank!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:41.44,0:20:42.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Negative, doing it!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:42.68,0:20:46.66,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll have to spread{/bury/plant} three years' worth of fertilizer{/manure - I'd like to be more specific here, but choosing manure migh have unexpected implications} as well! \NSure as hell it's a plenty of work!{/I gotta get busy}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:46.66,0:20:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,So I came to you to ask for a helper!
Dialogue: 0,0:20:48.84,0:20:50.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Please let me help you!{/accept/choose me}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:49.50,0:20:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:56.04,0:20:58.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, you seem capable enough for that job.{/in that case, I'm picking/asking you.}{unsure, this sounds a bit like "for that much, I'm counting on you"}
Dialogue: 0,0:20:58.96,0:21:01.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's not waste any time.{might omit this for cps} \NFollow uncle Redbeard at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:01.21,0:21:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:21:02.26,0:21:04.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Forget it!{Don't need you anymore! }\NYou snooze — you lose!{lit is "first, let's see if it works or goes up in smokes" but "snooze-lose" sounds much more like the japanese line and makes just as much sense while I can't think of an adage that would translate it more accurately and also have that rhyme pattern. Maybe "all or nothing/sink or swim"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:21:04.18,0:21:07.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll see you again by fall. \NWith three years' worth of crop. Three years' worth!
Dialogue: 0,0:21:09.11,0:21:13.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Redbeard! You'll regret not listening to the elders, \Nwhen it's already too late!{年寄りの言うこと聞かないで、いまに泣くんだな}{unsure, lit is "not listening to seniors, don't cry now/at this moment"}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:16.36,0:22:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,A cute child, isn't she?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:19.00,0:22:22.67,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, the day will come, \Nwhen you get to see your sister again.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:29.84,0:22:32.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri, you're doing well, aren't you?{/not losing your spirits}
Dialogue: 0,0:22:45.62,0:22:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Sir, something happened?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.38,0:22:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Contracted a disease!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:49.86,0:22:51.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Your head hurts?
Dialogue: 0,0:22:52.00,0:22:54.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It's not about me. Rice. It's rice!
Dialogue: 0,0:22:54.25,0:22:55.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Look.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:59.02,0:23:01.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Those red speckles are the disease?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:01.61,0:23:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Exactly that!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:26.86,0:23:27.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Honey!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:28.94,0:23:32.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, honey! Is it true that they say our rice \Nhad contracted a disease?
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.41,0:23:34.58,Default,,0,0,0,,It's too late now.{/all screwed already/no good}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:34.58,0:23:35.83,Default,,0,0,0,,There should be something we can do!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:35.83,0:23:38.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Too late anyway. \NIt's like five years ago all over again.{/just like 5 years ago}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:45.25,0:23:49.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Haven't I told you \Nto drop those ventures{/stop being a charlatan} because of that?!
Dialogue: 0,0:23:49.13,0:23:53.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In your obsession of harvesting three years worth of rice, \Nyou've wasted three years worth of fertilizer!{/But you were so obsessed with harvesting three years' worth of rice, you've used/buried three years' worth of fertilizer already!}
Dialogue: 0,0:23:54.42,0:23:57.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And the old man was trying to talk you out, too!{/haven't grandfather told you to stop, too?}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:04.65,0:24:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right!
Dialogue: 0,0:24:06.61,0:24:10.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In the paddies{/fields} of Ihatovo, \Nthere's no other farmer quite of my magnitude!{イーハトーヴの野原で、指折り数えられる大百姓のおれが、}{Lit: in the field of ihatovo, counting on one's fingers, I'm a prominent peasant - I have no clue why he uses the fingers idiom here, it may also mean "count down days in anticipation" but that makes no sense, so I think it's rather something like "there are so few of us, you can count us with your fingers" like the rus sub suggests}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:10.88,0:24:12.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Like hell if this discourages me!{こんなことで参るか。}{/am I letting it get to me?}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:12.53,0:24:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! We'll try again{/Doing it} next year.{よし。来年こそやるぞ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:16.73,0:24:17.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Won't we?{/right}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:18.83,0:24:23.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, ever since you appeared at my place, \Nyou haven't had a single good night's sleep yet.{おまえおれのうちへ来てから、まだ一晩も寝たいくらい寝たことがないな}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:23.71,0:24:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Now! Be it even five or ten days, \Nyou can sleep all you want!{さあ、五日でも十日でもいいから、ぐうというくらい寝てしまえ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:28.33,0:24:30.97,Default,,0,0,0,,After that, I'll make sure to surprise you{/show you an interesting/funny} \Nwith a magic trick!{あとで、俺はおもしろい手品見せるからな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:30.97,0:24:35.14,Default,,0,0,0,,In the meantime,{/As a substitute,} the house is going {to survive }through next winter \Nwith nothing but buckwheat.{/soba}{その代わりことしの冬は、家じゅうそばばかり食うんだぞ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:35.14,0:24:37.25,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure like buckwheat, don't you?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:55.68,0:24:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll purge{mushikoroshi is steaming to death/steamroll/seethe/poison, but this doesn't involve any heating, let alone steaming. My best guess is, this verb is also used as "to insecticide"} this disease once and for all, now.{いま、この病気を蒸し殺して...}
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.58,0:25:00.66,Default,,0,0,0,,But how are you...?{/is it really...}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:01.37,0:25:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Dousing in oil kills diseased species?{/infected seeds die from kerosene?}{石油で病気の種が死ぬんですか}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:03.91,0:25:08.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, If a fellow had his head \Nkept into oil, he would die, too!{/even a man dies, if ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:20.85,0:25:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, Budori, it's finally time to make{i'm not quite sure what makida means here; maybe "sow", though more likely is "extrude"; besides, they end up making noodles in the very next scene} buckwheat noodles. \NOil run its course.{/down with the oil}{he says "oil is over" which may mean it's gone or has done its work; in the book, oryza is completely dead by this point and next they start sowing buckwheat though}
Dialogue: 0,0:25:24.73,0:25:25.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:36.57,0:25:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Budori!
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.18,0:25:40.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Come over for a second.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:40.12,0:25:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:25:58.45,0:26:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,My late son's room.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:02.97,0:26:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, our paddy is one-third smaller this year, \Nso it would be much less laborious to till.{ブドリ、ことしは沼ばたけは去年よりは三分の一減ったからな、仕事はよほどらくだ。}{to be fair, I don't know why they all use "numabatakeno" instead of "numaba" and I can't look it up to any avail either, but maybe it's some special paddy or something; upd: I guess it's just 沼畑 - still an unusual word, but a simple "paddy field"}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:08.98,0:26:14.19,Default,,0,0,0,,On that occasion, I want you to devote yourself fully{/with all your heart} \Nto studying the books my son used to read{ from now on}.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:14.19,0:26:18.32,Default,,0,0,0,,So that everyone who had laughed at me before, \Ncalling me a crank,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:18.32,0:26:23.37,Default,,0,0,0,,would go "WOW!" at the sight of the magnificent rice, \Nthat you'd help me grow.{そのかわりおまえは、おれの死んだ息子むすこの読んだ本をこれから一生けん命勉強して、いままでおれを山師だといってわらったやつらを、あっと言わせるような立派なオリザを作るくふうをしてくれ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:26.31,0:26:29.25,Default,,0,0,0,,If I'm a crank, \Nthen my head is in the clouds!{/If I'm an adventurer, then a big-time one!}{俺は山師でも大した山師なんだ}{unsure, maybe "an important adventurer/big game" or, indirectly, "the one whose ventures always pay off"}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:33.09,0:26:37.70,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&H161929&\3c&H6F6A75&\pos(260,295)\fs14\frx342\fry22\frz355\blur1}Kubo{クーボー}'s Earth Science{I'm too lazy to check this sign, would trust rus sub here}
Dialogue: 1,0:26:34.25,0:26:35.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Very well.
Dialogue: 1,0:26:35.59,0:26:36.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Will do my best.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:38.38,0:26:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Kubo, \NI have finished mixing the fertilizer.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.10,0:26:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,This won't do.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:44.35,0:26:48.48,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, professor Kubo \Nis running his own school{/college/university} in the city of Ihatovo.{impying he is an important guy}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:48.79,0:26:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I wish I would also be part of it.{/Wish I would also be studying there./Wish he would teach me/I could learn from him, too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:51.73,0:26:53.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that's how it should be, too?{/agree with me/thing this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:54.19,0:26:56.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'd really like to have more to study.{/wish I could study more}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.13,0:26:59.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, Ihatovo City is the largest one around.{he uses two different words for city here}
Dialogue: 0,0:26:56.37,0:26:59.48,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:26:59.45,0:27:03.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I can meet someone who knows a thing or two \Nabout dad, mom, and Neri.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:04.66,0:27:07.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I get it, I get it! Thanks.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:13.94,0:27:15.95,Default,,0,0,0,,{Brother }Budori, what is this thing for?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.26,0:27:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,For milling the grain.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:18.55,0:27:19.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:19.72,0:27:20.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes! Here!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:21.97,0:27:26.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to bother you, but would you go \Nto a neighboring village tomorrow to buy this?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:27.42,0:27:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure... But what kind of thing is that?{/what is that for}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:29.68,0:27:33.52,Default,,0,0,0,,If they don't have it there, \Nkeep going through towns and villages until you find it.{/try looking for it in other ... as well}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:33.52,0:27:35.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay… But what about my work?
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.32,0:27:39.60,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you talking about? \NThis year, we are all completely out of work{/free}.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:35.60,0:27:39.69,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:42.66,0:27:45.58,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(0,500)\pos(420,67)\blur1\fs13\frx24\fry334\frz11\c&H1A2027&\3c&H637893&}Bus stop{this resembles "noriba" so I guess it makes sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:27:54.79,0:27:56.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Rice contracted a disease again!
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.01,0:28:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,If even the oil treatment is futile{/of no result}, \Nwhat else should I try?{this "orentokono" construction in the beginning is unfamiliar to me, my guess is "of all things I've tried"}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:01.47,0:28:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me give it a try this time.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:03.44,0:28:04.60,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.60,0:28:06.58,Default,,0,0,0,,I think, I can make it work.{/I may be up to something/I can do something with it}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:09.42,0:28:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright! Go ahead{ and try}!
Dialogue: 0,0:28:10.98,0:28:12.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks a lot.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:12.31,0:28:13.38,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:13.56,0:28:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Redbeard, \Nare you sure about giving it a go?{/Hey, Redbeard, are you sure we should go that far?}{/are you out of your mind, to allow such a thing}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.91,0:28:34.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, Budori, what is that thing?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:34.29,0:28:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Wood ash and salt.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:37.88,0:28:39.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that'd kill the disease?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:40.30,0:28:42.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Can it really cut the job?{Can it really be killed this way?}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.31,0:28:50.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, any progress?{/how is it looking}{it sounds like he is asking "how is salt"}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:50.35,0:28:52.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, the disease is apparently suppressed.{/somehow, the disease is contained}{this sounds like 防ぎ which is "prevent/defend"}
Dialogue: 0,0:28:53.48,0:28:54.20,Default,,0,0,0,,What?!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:00.74,0:29:01.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You did it,{/it worked} Budori!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:02.76,0:29:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:06.00,0:29:06.78,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.45,0:29:08.45,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.45,0:29:10.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori did it!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.70,0:29:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,I have been dismissed as a crank for four years straight, \Nbut now I'll have four years worth in one go!{Well, would you look at that — for four years, I have been dismissed/failed/made a blunder as an adventurer, but this year, I'll harvest four years' worth in one go!}{なんの、おれも、山師で四年しくじったけれども、ことしは一度に四年分とれる}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:32.93,0:29:34.54,Default,,0,0,0,,{/This goes beyond my expectations!}This is rather good enough, too!{これもまたなかなかいいもんだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:34.54,0:29:40.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I was frankly skeptical myself, \Nuntil Budori came into picture to save your bacon!{I was wondering at one point, what would come out of this, until suddenly, Budori came into picture to save your bacon!}{全く一時はどうなるかと思ったけどあんたんところのブドリはたいしたもんだ}{/there was a time when I was thinking "what shall he do about this," but having mr. Budori by your side turned out to be a valuable asset/a big deal}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:35.09,0:29:40.55,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:40.48,0:29:41.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, dead right!
Dialogue: 0,0:29:41.61,0:29:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus,{it's my guess for that "sonrya" part} the crank's estimates \N{it's the same word as the one used when budori first met redbeard} were without mistake!{/there was no miscalculation}
Dialogue: 0,0:29:52.29,0:29:54.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. Have a snack too, Budori.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:55.54,0:29:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Mistress{女将}, thank you for everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:59.00,0:30:02.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You have helped me a great deal \Nin locating my family.{/You did me a great deal of help looking for my family.}{/you made in possible for me to look for my family}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.08,0:30:04.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you saying? \NI was just...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:04.63,0:30:06.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I am grateful, deeply.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:07.09,0:30:11.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh my, you are such a gentleman.{/what is wrong with you?} \NBy the way,{/while we're at it,} did you learn something?{まったくあんたときたらそれで何か分かったのか}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:14.60,0:30:16.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.{/regrettable}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.31,0:30:18.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You really are a wonderful boy.{あんたは本当にいい青年だ}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.77,0:30:21.02,Default,,0,0,0,,If only my son had still been alive...
Dialogue: 0,0:30:21.40,0:30:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, if you'd like it better, our doors...{ブドリさんあなたよかったらうちの}{/if possible, could you stay by our place?}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:24.74,0:30:27.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, mistress, we're out of booze!{we've discussed this line in #board-room}
Dialogue: 0,0:30:55.02,0:31:00.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Budori, I used to be \None of the most prominent farmers of Ihatovo.{ブドリ、おれももとはイーハトーヴの大百姓だったし}{/major peasants}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.60,0:31:03.37,Default,,0,0,0,,I came here with a sizeable seed capital.{/start-up capital/There was a time when my household was considerable/I came a long way of many transformations}{ずいぶんかせいでも来たのだが - kasei is breaking my head apart because it's in hiragana here and may mean, akhem: housekeeping/household economy/growth; metamorphosis/assistance; backing; reinforcements}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.63,0:31:11.24,Default,,0,0,0,,{/Lately, due to consecutive droughts and frosts, my paddy shrank to one third of its former size.}But as for now, with droughts and frosts following one after another, my paddy shrank to one third of its former size.{このところたびたびの旱魃と寒さのために、いまじゃ沼ばたけも三分の一になってしまった}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:13.37,0:31:17.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't even have any fertilizer left for{/to use/put it} next year.{来年はもう入れるこやしもないのだ}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:21.67,0:31:22.89,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's not just us.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.89,0:31:28.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Within Ihatovo, there's hardly anyone \Nable to afford fertilizer for the next year.{/In the entire of Ihatovo, there's hardly a handful of those who can afford fertilizer for the next year.}{/there won't be anyone able to buy and put in the ground the fertilizer next year anymore}{れだけでない。来年こやしを買って入れれる人ったらもうイーハトーヴにも何人もないだろう。}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:28.55,0:31:29.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's how it is.{/the deal/situation}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:30.49,0:31:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,In the light of this{/these circumstances}, there's no telling when I will, \Nif ever, be able to repay{/thank you} for your labor{/hard work on my behalf}.{こういうあんばいでは、いつになっておまえにはたらいてもらった礼をするというあてもない}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:36.72,0:31:41.85,Default,,0,0,0,,It'd be such a pity for you to slave away \Nthe prime of your youth in the boondocks!{おまえも若い働き盛りを、おれのとこで暮らしてしまってはあんまり気の毒だ}{/it pains me to see you, still young, waste your peak years working vainly in my place}
Dialogue: 0,0:31:48.99,0:31:55.33,Default,,0,0,0,,It pains me to say, but you should take this \Nand try to seek your fortune somewhere less hopeless.{済まないがどうかこれを持って、どこへでも行っていい運を見つけてくれ。}{/I'm sorry to ask you, but have this and try looking for good luck elsewhere/may you have good luck by your side wherever you go in your quest}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.16,0:32:20.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Somehow, I'm sure, \Nyou'll find your own safe haven!{Somewhere, I'm sure, you'll find a safe harbor of your own!}{きっとどこかで無事で暮らしてるよ}{/certainly, theres a place for you to live a safe/peaceful/carefree life}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:27.73,0:32:29.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the cry of a turtledove{https://ja.wikipedia.org/wiki/%E3%82%AD%E3%82%B8%E3%83%90%E3%83%88}{maybe just "dove" to not fall into wikifaggotry?}.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.99,0:32:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Though Neri's was head and shoulders above mine.{/was so much better in doing this}
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.80,0:32:34.97,Default,,0,0,0,,When I do this, \Nit's like we're reunited{together/she's by my side again}.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.47,0:33:42.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Ihatovo. Ihatovo. Terminus!
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.10,0:33:49.61,Sign,,0,0,0,,Ihatovo. Ihatovo. Those changing trains, please hurry.{/transferring passengers ...}{お乗り換えの方はお急ぎください}
Dialogue: 1,0:33:44.10,0:33:47.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry to trouble you, little one, \Nbut please make way.{/open the road}
Dialogue: 1,0:33:47.60,0:33:48.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:51.20,0:33:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.44,0:33:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry, but don't you happen to know \Nabout {Professor }Kubo's school?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:55.74,0:33:56.45,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:57.31,0:33:58.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see...
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.38,0:34:00.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, dear.{/You, can you spare us a moment, lady?}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.91,0:34:03.33,Default,,0,0,0,,This boy is looking for Kubo's school.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:03.33,0:34:04.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you know anything?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.56,0:34:05.16,Default,,0,0,0,,I do!{/yes}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:05.16,0:34:09.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, my! Hey, hey, \Nyou should ask this lady to help you.{/this lady/person knows how to help you/something/about it - wanted to make it continuous with the next line which has distinctive "yes"}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:09.27,0:34:09.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:11.13,0:34:13.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Kubo's{this sounds like "kurugo" because of distortion} school is a fine one.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.03,0:34:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It does a great job \Nconnecting those starved for knowledge.{I had to guess half of the words here, my best variant is 学びたい気持ちの人達はいいな集まるの, or, less likely, "なんだ見たい" in the beginning. Roughly, it's "various people who feel they want to learn/study all get along/assemble/come together there"}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:16.32,0:34:17.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:18.47,0:34:20.68,Default,,0,0,0,,There, it's inside that forest{ over there}.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:20.68,0:34:22.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Look for a big white building.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:22.39,0:34:24.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay. Thanks a lot for showing the way.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.82,0:34:25.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Best of luck.{/do your best}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:26.64,0:34:28.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:30.06,0:34:33.92,Default,,0,0,0,,With that in mind, \Nwe arrive to the following conclusion...{this one still makes sense as a lection, more or less. the following lines, though, are an excerpt from miyazawa's "Spring & Asura" poetry omnibus, that don't make a terribly lot of sense, as far as poetry is concerned, but I tried to make them sensible, rhymey and lyrical at the same time. Unfortunately, I found no way to make them into a consecutive lection without making stuff up like the rus sub did. Might as well replace altogether with an oblique/obscure quote from shakespear/betjeman etc}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:33.92,0:34:39.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The short moments of resting from work\NI spent crying, absorbing the musings {/engraving the studying} into my soul.{わずかの仕事のひまで泣きながら　からだに刻んでいく勉強が　ぐんぐん強い芽を噴いて　どこまでのびるかわからない\N それがこれからの新しい学問の始まりなんだ。}{it's mostly written in kana and thus makes me scratch out a new bold spot on my head: miyazawa was a renowned master of onomatopy and this was probably intentional as I encounter many words that lie well with the context in both their meanings so don't be surprised at my supposed alternative lines being as radically alternative to one another as the third alternative was to the communist economics}{/in the few days until it was the day of work, I carved studying in my body while crying,}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:39.56,0:34:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,{Afterwards, }Strong buds shoot from it, \Nthough there's no telling how high they can climb.{/until the ever-strengthening hand wipes my eyes, though I can't know how far it can go}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.23,0:34:48.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus, I believe, a new field of study rooted{/is to be born}.{/That's the beginning of the new studies to come.}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:45.20,0:34:46.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.08,0:34:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello?
Dialogue: 0,0:34:48.79,0:34:50.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello!
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.75,0:34:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You there sure is a noisy{vociferous/noisy/boisterous} fellow, \Nbut I'm in the middle of a class!{やかましいやつだ。今授業中だよ}
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.55,0:34:58.24,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have business with me, \N{\i1}you{\i0} join us inside and pipe it down!{don't try to drag me outside}{trying to make this line sound comedic so as to tie it up with the following laughter}{用があるなら君の方からはいって来い}{/If you have business with me, the initiative is yours to come my way/it's your side that has to go out of your way for this/just enter under your own itiative}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.39,0:35:07.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Eight Gamma, E{unsure about this because I feel it'd be more correct to put I - iota in here, but he refers to as is "I" and not the full name like to other letters. IF this is a letter at all, and not japanese "ii" or something else} six, Alpha{/8γ e6, α}.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.14,0:35:10.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Particularly striking example \Nis the Large Magellanic Cloud.{/Of particular interest is the Magellan Nebula}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:10.77,0:35:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Using the light, all the plants can redox{I know photosynthesis is not a reduction reaction and also there's a separate word for "redox" in Japanese, but I'm at the end of my wits} glucose \Nin their chlorophyll-containing lateral buds.{This is the longest shot I ever did in my tranlations. Ever. I don't know where to start about this line. My best guesses with various probabilities are \N 草みんな能力そう回復しブドウ糖を含むゲッコの腋芽 / 嚏な葉緑素大服しブドウ糖を含む月光の腋芽  / 臭みな葉緑素回復しブドウ糖を含む月光の駅が - this makes zero sense each way, but there's hardly a variant that doesn't; I'll try to crack down the least zany variant I could assemble from of all the options of the words I'm not sure about, which are "kusamina, kaifukushi, fukumu, gekko, eki": All the (minna) herbs/grass/plants (kusa) can recover/restore (kaifukushi) chlorophyll (youryokuso), in glucose (budoutou)-containing (wo fukumu) moonlight (gekkou no) lateral buds (ekiga)}{At this point, I have no idea if this entire lecture is meant to be a hotchpotch of schizophasic gibberish or not, but up until now lines were at least consequent and sensible within borders defined by the sentence. This one, however, I can't make into a logically consistent construction. I'm no biology major but even I can tell the moonlight can't trigger the Photosynthesis; Rus sub made shit up here as well. Also chlorophyll is not just in lateral buds, but I'm washing my hands at this point. Kusamina may also mean stinky/sneezy, and gekko may be... well, gecko, while eki is also "train station."}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:16.19,0:35:19.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, you can say they are effectively \Ntugging at heartstrings{/pulsating}. {my guess is まあ喜びの脈を奏でているのである, unsure about myaku but the rest is solid so it's "playing on ... (some musical instrument) of joy/exhilaration" either way, myaku is "vein/pulse" so I figured might as well be string}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:30.29,0:35:35.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the "History of History" mock-up, \Ndescribed in Mr.{"professor" would be fitting here, however, context suggests he knows this man is a professor, but budori doesn't know kubo is a professor, too, check the line at 36:12} Kubo's book?{あれはくーぼうという人の本の中に書いてあった歴史の歴史の模型だ - lit: is that the ... model about which it was written in the book by the man going by the name of kubo; also "history of history" is a more fitting name for a book, not a maquette, but it seems it's the name of the contraption itself}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:40.68,0:35:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a ship now!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:43.72,0:35:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,And now...{/again}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:47.37,0:35:48.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's{/looks just like} a centipede{mukade}!
Dialogue: 0,0:35:49.17,0:35:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a cool one!{/so great}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.11,0:35:53.97,Default,,0,0,0,,And thus, for a case like that...{だからこういう場合}
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.57,0:35:59.32,Default,,0,0,0,,We can produce a diagram like that.{こういう図ができるのである}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:06.44,0:36:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.44,0:36:09.86,Default,,0,0,0,,You really hope to redraw that diagram from scratch?{はじめから、この図なんか書けるもんか - I'm really unsure about the role of hajime here, maybe it's "from the first part of the drawing/fully" or "from your first attendance here/after you just started attending", also "monka" is "is there such a thing" which may imply something I'm not quite grasping, too. Rus sub suggests "how did you manage to copy that blueprint in the first try" but that's bullshit}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:12.11,0:36:14.28,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the name of that professor?{/how is he called; the trick with this wording is that it may imply "what kind of professor/what subject is he teaching"}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:14.28,0:36:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:15.54,0:36:17.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the{he uses "dai" which is even cooler than just a professor} Professor Kubo!
Dialogue: 0,0:36:17.88,0:36:19.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know even this{little}?{/you don't know that, too?}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.92,0:36:24.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't even know that, \Nhow can you hope to understand anything?{/what in the world can you understand [of his teachings]}{/how long can you fare?}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:24.19,0:36:27.17,Default,,0,0,0,,It took me six years of listening \Nto the very same lectures!{ぼくでさえ同じ講義をもう六年もきいているんだ}{/Even I have been listening to the same lecture for six years now}{I'm clueless as to what he means to imply by that - only 6 years later he started to understand or that even he still doesn't understand, or that it can't be understood and you just have to keep listening, etc}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:32.27,0:36:35.02,Default,,0,0,0,,As for now, the evening is well underway.{いまや夕べははるかにきたり}{/we're far behing the evening now/it came a long time ago}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:36.09,0:36:38.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This also concludes my course of lectures.{拙講もまた全課をおえた。}{/I have, again, concluded all of my lessons}{unsure about sekkou here, even though I have the text for certain, it's an unusual construction with no dictionary definition}
Dialogue: 0,0:36:38.48,0:36:42.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Those of you{, gentlemen,} who wish to apply for the scholarship{added, original is just "to become candidates"}, \Nmust indeed{not sure why this affirmation is here, it's "kedashi"}, as per our custom,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:42.49,0:36:46.84,Default,,0,0,0,,present{shimeshi is lesson; discipline; example (e.g. set a bad example)​/ revelation so I'm not sure why he uses it this exact way} the notebooks to yours truly, \Nand after a few{this he clearly says "suuko" but the book says "suuka" and it's also a rare word not on jisho, seems just a fancy way to say "several/various" to me} further{/additional} examinations{/questions} passed{ukete is "receive/defend/sustain" and I'm not sure which eng word to use},
Dialogue: 0,0:36:46.84,0:36:49.06,Default,,0,0,0,,we will decide on your affiliation{/determine where you belong to}.{諸君のうちの希望者は、けだしいつもの例により、ノートをば拙者に示し、さらに数箇の試問を受けて、所属を決すべきである}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:24.86,0:37:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent. This diagram \Nis remarkably faithful to the original{/extraordinarily accurate}.{よろしい。この図は非常に正しくできている。}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:28.42,0:37:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,And what in the world{/the heck} is that part?{そのほかのところは、なんだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:30.29,0:37:34.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see.{this really is just :hahaa:} This paddy fertilizer part{still unsure about "batakeno" part}, \Nor{this sounds rather like "the thing about food for horses inside the thing about paddy fertilizers" but I don't suppose that was the case, though I'd have thought twice had they been talking about horse shit and not food} the one about horse forage...{ははあ、沼ばたけのこやしのことに、馬のたべ物のこと。}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:37.31,0:37:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Then I should ask you to answer this:{/answer a question please}{では問題に答えなさい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:39.25,0:37:44.42,Default,,0,0,0,,When a factory's fireplace is lit,{added to tie up with the next "added to tie up" part} do you know{added to tie up with budori saying "yes" next; originally it's just "what kinds ... are there"} \Nthe colors{he just says "the types of colors" but that seems redundant since "different colors" implies that already so I changed it} of smoke curls leaving the chimney?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:44.42,0:37:49.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Black, gray, yellow, brown{褐色}, colorless. \NIt's a mixture of those.{/those are preeminent}{unsure if he means "the smoke always consists of them" or "sometimes, the smoke is a mixture of some of those"}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:49.91,0:37:52.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You mentioned colorless{ smoke}, very good.{/it's very important/great/remarkable that you know about/mentioned the colorless one/colorless is big deal/very good}{無色のけむりはたいへんいい}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:52.35,0:37:54.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Care to tell me about the shapes?{/please tell me what you know about their form}{/形について言いたまえ}
Dialogue: 0,0:37:54.48,0:37:55.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure!
Dialogue: 0,0:37:57.46,0:38:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,In a windless weather{/if there's no wind}, the smoke, accordingly{/as an appropriate answer}, \Nrises vertically{/rises straight up to form a rod/pole}, as the dome{/upper part} tends to disperse.{/the tip of the pole is gradually widening/further up it spreads more sideways}{無風で煙が相当あれば、たての棒にもなりますが、さきはだんだんひろがります。}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:02.80,0:38:08.20,Default,,0,0,0,,On the days with clouds hovering low, the plume{/pole} \Nfirst rises towards them, then starts to disperse sideways.{雲の非常に低い日は、棒は雲までのぼって行って、そこから横にひろがります。}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:08.53,0:38:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,On windy days, the plume slants{/becomes slanted/goes up in an obliquely(?)}, \Nwith the tilt angle in direct relation to the wind velocity{/the degree of that slope depends on the speed of wind}.{風のある日は、棒は斜めになりますが、その傾きは風の速度に従います。}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:14.35,0:38:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,The plume is subjected to the vagaries of the wind, \Nif it blows in a wavy or linear way.{/The pole abides strictly the will of the wind \Nin how wavy or continuous it is./it's up to the wind to define how many waves it'll have or in how many pieces it'll be cut (I hope that's the meaning of "ikutsu kire ni naru" here)}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:18.04,0:38:20.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But fume{didn't wanna overuse the "smoke" here} and chimney peculiarities{/habits that ... have/the smoke's nature and the shape of the chimney} \Nalso get a say{/factor} in it.{he used a strong "defined strictly by the will" for the wind, but uses less definitive "up to smoke and chimney" without "yorimasu" here}{波やいくつもきれになるのは、風のためにもよりますが、一つはけむりや煙突のもつ癖のためです。}{I'm still clueless as for the role of "hitotsu" here, maybe it's like "one of the factors" or "the one small thing that also defines it is ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:21.34,0:38:25.34,Default,,0,0,0,,When the smoke output is negligible{/not very massive}, \Nit assumes the corkscrew shape.{あまり煙の少ないときは、コルク抜きの形にもなり、}{/in the times there's not much of smoke, it leaves [the chimney] in spirals}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:25.34,0:38:30.14,Default,,0,0,0,,And if some heavy gas is mixed in{ the smoke}, \Nit tufts after exiting the chimney's vent.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:30.14,0:38:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It then rushes downwards, \Nin one or all directions.{/Then spreads along the ground, in one or all directions at once.}{煙も重いガスがまじれば、煙突の口から房ふさになって、一方ないし四方におちることもあります。}{/if there are heavy gases in the smoke, from the chimney's mouth, it becomes bushy and then falls down (I wish to somehow include this "descend" more explicitly in this line) in directions ranging from one to all/to four cardinal directions}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:38.77,0:38:39.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Excellent.{/all right}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:40.23,0:38:42.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You're no stranger to labor, are you?{again, to tie up with the following "hai", real is "what kind of job you're doing?"}{よろしい。きみはどういう仕事をしているのか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:42.94,0:38:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I arrived here to look for one.{仕事をみつけに来たんです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.30,0:38:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,I have a{n interesting} job just for you.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:46.95,0:38:50.47,Default,,0,0,0,,With my business card, \Nyou can head there at once{/commute more easily}.{/おもしろい仕事がある。名刺をあげるから、そこへすぐ行きなさい。}{/I'll give you my recommendation, so depart immediately for that place}
Dialogue: 0,0:38:54.16,0:38:55.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, here it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:55.74,0:38:57.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you so much!
Dialogue: 0,0:38:57.71,0:38:58.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, if you excuse me.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:05.42,0:39:08.08,Default,,0,0,0,,The heck? They are burning their garbage now?{なんだ、ごみでも焼いてるのかな。}{I genuinely wish I'd known what this is about, but there's no room for misinterpretation. Unlike some other weird lines from the book, nobody even seems to question it, it's like the most natural thing to appear in this place and time in the book while to me it seems the most blatant ever defiance of the chekhov's gun rule. I don't see how this can be a joke or a pun either. The nearest stretch I can think of is "he saw someone burning trash (albeit why does he even care, or what's the point? not to mention nobody had any idea burning garbage is baddy-baddy for at least half a century after miyazawa's death) that he managed to determine as trash thanks to his unrivaled knowledge about sorts of fumes (dafuq), so he flew off to that place to sort this out (although there's not a single smoke on the next frame of him leaving into the sunset)"}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.08,0:39:08.87,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry?
Dialogue: 0,0:39:10.43,0:39:12.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Around that neighborhood.{/somewhere in that area}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:12.55,0:39:14.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right...
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.64,0:39:16.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Watch out!{maybe replace with "what are you doing" or something else since the man was clearly "watching out" anyway?}
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.68,0:39:53.76,Default,,0,0,0,,If I sort out the job question,{/manage to decide on the issue of employment} \Nto study won't be an issue{/I would be able to study, too}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:53.76,0:39:56.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe I'll even get a chance \Nto look for dad, mom, and Neri{ guys}.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:56.89,0:39:59.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I need that appointment, whatever it takes.{doubting that line, but don't see better options, yatotte seems to be "hiring/empoying" but it's not a reflexive verb by itself, it can hardly be used as "get myself hired" while "moranakucha" seems to mean either "to receive/to get someone to do something" or "to defend/to secure/to abide/to fit" both of which make sense if you think about it, yet I can't help feeling something's off here}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:02.59,0:40:11.11,Sign,,0,0,0,,Volcanology University
Dialogue: 1,0:40:08.61,0:40:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Oops, sorry, little one! My bad!
Dialogue: 0,0:40:18.85,0:40:21.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Is it for an official business{ with someone}?{he really fucking likes his "yes" after being asked doesn't he}{/Which department you have a business with/section [of organization] did you come to visit?}{it sounds a bit ridiculous to ask if a child has an official business, but in a movie like this, in a place like this... is it really that ridiculous anymore?}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.08,0:40:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:21.87,0:40:23.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You see...
Dialogue: 0,0:40:23.71,0:40:25.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, this is it.{/this is my business/I'm here for this}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:25.67,0:40:28.99,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\c&HE8E2DC&\3c&H5C4A42&\pos(350,299)\frz1\blur1}Reception{believing russub here}
Dialogue: 1,0:40:27.51,0:40:28.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, follow me this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:29.26,0:40:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's why I'm telling you it won't work!{/therefore, I don't think this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:33.53,0:40:35.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's put it to the test again.{/Let's study/investigate/keep an eye on it just a little longer.}
Dialogue: 0,0:40:48.57,0:40:49.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You go that way.{/it's here}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:07.54,0:41:09.67,Default,,0,0,0,,It's still too early for that.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:43.96,0:41:45.00,Default,,0,0,0,,I beg your pardon.{/sorry for making you wait}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.45,0:41:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You must be that Gusko Budori guy.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:47.48,0:41:49.75,Default,,0,0,0,,And here is my business card.{/You can address to me this way/I'm this kind of the deal}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:50.49,0:41:55.49,Default,,0,0,0,,"Volcanology University chief engineer, Pennen Nam?"{火山局技師ペンネンナーム}
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.91,0:42:00.14,Default,,0,0,0,,I got a call from Professor Kubo not long ago,{/recently} \Nso I've been waiting for you.{さきほどクーボー博士から電話があったのでお待ちしていたところです。}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:00.14,0:42:03.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Starting now, you can work and study here with us.{he actually says "study [elsewhere] while working here" but if we use "university" interpretation, why not} \NHow about that?{/how do you like that prospect}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:03.94,0:42:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, {\i1}here?{\i0}{heck if I know what he meant to say by that; it sounds like he is implying "sorry, but what kind of place is this" which clearly can't be the case so I think it's rather he is doubting his qualification for working in such a place}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.91,0:42:08.77,Default,,0,0,0,,This place only opened up{/started bustling} last year.{albeit it sounds like "this place's work only began last year" it may be "I started working here ..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:09.23,0:42:15.82,Default,,0,0,0,,To tell you the truth,{/and, in reality/actually} it is a highly responsible job, conducted half of the time on a volcano that may erupt at any moment.{ここの仕事は、去年はじまったばかりですが、じつに責任のあるもので、それに半分はいつ噴火するかわからない火山の上で仕事するものなのです。}{/it takes one a lot of responsibility/this place can be hold accountable for all sorts of things and you have to spend half of your time upon a volcano that you don't know when is going to erupt}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:16.67,0:42:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides, the behavioral patterns of a volcano \Nis still a major enigma of Science.{それに火山の癖というものは、なかなか学問でわかることではないのです。}{/in addition, things like volcanoes' habits/tendencies is pretty much/rather not something the study/branch of science can understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:22.41,0:42:25.91,Default,,0,0,0,,We will need to redouble effort \Nto our duties, from now on.{/We are all going to have to take a tighter grip on our duties, from now on.}{われわれはこれからよほどしっかりやらなければならんのです。}{/from now on, we have to do/perform [our work] by a great extent more dilligently}{why is it only "from now on"? beats fucking me. Implying "now that you join us", maybe?}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:26.50,0:42:28.39,Default,,0,0,0,,{heck if I know why is he seething here, as though he was just insulted or something. maybe, like, he's mad at volcanoes for making him abandon his home?}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.54,0:42:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,What do you say? \NCan you do it?{/will you manage}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:31.74,0:42:32.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:42:32.67,0:42:34.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Glad to be working with you!{/please take care of me}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:34.84,0:42:37.47,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. Let us both do our best, \Nstarting now.{/let's work hard together}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.80,0:42:38.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, this way.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:40.39,0:42:43.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Yonder, there's a room{/place} for you to stay \Nfrom tonight-on.{/starting tonight, we have an accommodation over there for you to live}{man this guy sure loves to point out "from now on" and I'm out of options for phrasing this some way not hackneyed}{今晩からあっちにあなたの泊まるところがありますから、}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:44.70,0:42:47.48,Default,,0,0,0,,For the remainder{rest is used later in that line so had to circumvent} of the day, \Nuse that room to get a proper rest.{/get a good rest/muster some strength over there}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:47.88,0:42:51.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, tomorrow, \NI'll show you every corner of this facility{/Then, tomorrow, I'll give you a complete tour of the building.}{/institution; he uses building, but later they have all sorts of annexes, so I think this fits more}.{/give you a complete/thorough tour through this building}{あしたこの建物の中をすっかり案内しますから。}
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.08,0:42:51.43,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:51.44,0:42:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:35.23,0:43:38.18,Default,,0,0,0,,This concludes your first look at the organization.{これで一通りの説明は終わりました}{/With this, the general/usual/all-inclusive/superficial explanation/description/account is over}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:49.29,0:43:51.62,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, did I tire you out?{/are you tired}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:51.62,0:43:57.55,Default,,0,0,0,,No, it's just that I'm deeply impressed{/affected/moved/overwhelmed} with your incredible equipment{/installations} and your research efforts in various fields{/branches}.{/No, the incredible sight of the facilities and your research efforts in various fields just overwhelmed me.}
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.84,0:44:02.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, Ihatovo alone \Nis a home to over 300 volcanoes.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:02.72,0:44:08.29,Default,,0,0,0,,So one can spend his life away just studying \Nhow they impact{/affect} people's lives, each in its own way.{/and one by one, in various forms, they bestow their influence upon folks' livelyhood}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:08.89,0:44:12.80,Default,,0,0,0,,What you and me are struggling{/dealing/fighting} with{/our opponent/counterpart} \Nis not just volcanoes, but the very nature{/the nature itself}.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:13.19,0:44:15.31,Default,,0,0,0,,And that struggle has yet merely started.{/and we're only in the beginning of that path}{/It is all just a mere start, deep we are in riddles.}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.31,0:44:16.90,Default,,0,0,0,,We're knee-deep in riddles.{/There are more questions than answers/it's full of things we don't understand}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.90,0:44:20.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, one at a time, we approach them, \Nbuild new machinery to better comprehend{for solving them}.{struggling with the wording here, all this can be turned many ways: one by one, we're inventing/working out the way/coming up [with solution], for that purpose, produce mechanisms/instruments}{でも一つずつ工夫をし、そのための機会を作り}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.74,0:44:24.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And in the end, we don't even get any choice, \Nbut to observe and move on.{そして観察していかなければいけないと思うんですよ}{kansatsu can only be observation; survey; watching, but what's the point of this speech if he doesn't convey any point by that}{/so I think we should just observe}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:24.70,0:44:29.00,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, it took the entities we're struggling with{/the opponent} \N{god knows how many }millions of years to get where they are now.{なにせ相手は何百万年もかけて今あるんですからねぇ}{/After all, we deal with fellows million of years older than us.}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:30.50,0:44:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I see now.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.64,0:44:34.33,Default,,0,0,0,,What happened to dad, mom, and Neri... \NAnd uncle Redbeard.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:35.21,0:44:38.66,Default,,0,0,0,,If only I could deliver everyone \Nfrom hardships they lived through...{this is very vague, Lit: "everyone live their lives without that kind of suffering"}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:39.42,0:44:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,To do that, I must keep studying.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.80,0:44:45.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Try harder, harder, in this place.{unsure, motto is just "more", maybe "more than before/than what I'm already doing"}
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.73,0:44:58.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Shoots!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.55,0:45:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:05.99,0:45:06.87,Default,,0,0,0,,There you are!{/found it}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:08.53,0:45:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Morning, everyone!
Dialogue: 0,0:45:12.83,0:45:14.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Good morning, Budori.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.62,0:45:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, can you take care of that?{/sorry, please do that thing for me} Thanks{sorry rhymes with budori so that'll sound bad, replaced with other agent of politeness}.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:28.53,0:45:29.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.64,0:45:36.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Done.{/finished}\NA little deviation{/measurement error; calculation error} is starting to manifest{/it is starting to show ...}.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:37.56,0:45:40.15,Default,,0,0,0,,I think we should at least notify \Nthe second floor guys.{/maybe let them know it on the second floor, too, once}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:40.15,0:45:42.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Sure, I will go there at once{/now}.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:42.90,0:45:43.80,Default,,0,0,0,,You sure?{/if you say so}
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.80,0:45:45.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, I'll be on my way.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:45.91,0:45:46.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:57.98,0:46:02.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, but it's better \Nthat you change the settings on this one a bit.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.05,0:46:04.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Let me see.{/what's that}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:04.76,0:46:06.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It manifests down there{/on the lower floors}, too?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:06.59,0:46:07.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:07.18,0:46:08.82,Default,,0,0,0,,I see. \NWe'll {\fsp0.2}{for whatever reason, f merges with i in that font, so use this command to cleave them if need be}fix{/do} it now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.82,0:46:09.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Please do.{/count on you}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:09.95,0:46:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you, Budori.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:11.34,0:46:12.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{if you }Excuse me!{/I'll be going}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:23.05,0:46:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, it's still at it{/up to something/not right/active}?{unsure, may mean all sorts of things, like "budori, you're still here" or "is it doing it again?"}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:24.75,0:46:25.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:25.51,0:46:28.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Very concerning.{/I'm very worried about it} \NIt has been this way for about 5 minutes now.{/it has been in this state since about 5 minutes ago}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:29.10,0:46:31.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Sanmutori has been dormant{fast asleep/dead quiet} \Nup to this morning.{/has never shown any signs/been active .../nothing indicated sanmutori ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.66,0:46:36.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. I have never seen Sanmutori active{/working/fuctioning/operating/awake}{hataraita may suggest that it's not a volcano that's working, but rather its sensors/detecting machinery} \Nup until now.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.46,0:46:39.17,Default,,0,0,0,,This must be an impending eruption.{/this is also an imminent/closing in/approaching eruption}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:39.93,0:46:42.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Ten kilometers north of this mountain{/volcano} \Nis the city of Sanmutori.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.88,0:46:44.01,Default,,0,0,0,,If it explodes{bakuhatsu's primary meaning is explode but it may mean erupt as well} now{added},
Dialogue: 0,0:46:44.01,0:46:49.04,Default,,0,0,0,,Scorias the size of a table or a cow\Nand hot gas with ashes will pour over Sanmutori.{/rocks the size of a cow or a table, along with the sizzling-hot ash and gas will precipitate on Sanmutori.}{爆発すれば、たぶん牛やテーブルぐらいの岩は熱い灰やガスといっしょに、サンムトリ市におちてくる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:50.04,0:46:55.08,Default,,0,0,0,,At any rate, the only thing we can do now \Nis to drill an aperture seawards to release the gas.{/In any case, the only thing we can do now is to drill/pierce/make \Nan aperture/wound/opening in the side facing the sea to release/let go the gas.}{どうでも今のうちに、海に向いたほうへ傷口をこさえて、ガスを抜かなければならない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.39,0:46:56.84,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going{/let's go} there{ together} at once{/right now}!{今すぐ二人で行こう。}
Dialogue: 0,0:46:56.84,0:46:57.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:00.74,0:47:01.73,Default,,0,0,0,,This is Budori.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:01.73,0:47:04.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Me and Pennen head out at once \Nfor{/towards} Sanmutori volcano.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:04.51,0:47:06.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Please take care of everything{ for me}.{/I count on you}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:20.21,0:47:22.00,Sign,,0,0,0,,Volcanology University
Dialogue: 0,0:47:34.34,0:47:38.41,Default,,0,0,0,,{/By your reckoning, do you know how long is it until the eruption?}Your reckoning have something to say \Nabout the time we have until the eruption?{/きみはこの山はあと何日ぐらいで噴火すると思うかね。}{/how do you think, in how many days this mountain will explode?}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.41,0:47:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. A month, I think.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:40.14,0:47:41.19,Default,,0,0,0,,A month?!
Dialogue: 0,0:47:41.19,0:47:42.73,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't be more than 10 days!{/we have less than 10 days already/it won't last another 10 days}{もう十日ももたない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:42.73,0:47:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If we don't get to work fast, \Nit will be beyond saving!{早く工作してしまわないと、取り返しのつかないことになる。}{/if we don't start handling it/the construction works soon, it will be irreversible/cannot be undone}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:46.36,0:47:50.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sure, yonder is the thinnest part \Nof the slope{/wall} facing the sea.{私はこの山の海に向いたほうでは、あすこがいちばん弱いと思う。}{Lit: I think, there, towards the sea-facing side, this mountain is the weakest}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:50.57,0:47:53.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It should have no more than two layers of lava.{あすこは熔岩の層が二つしかない。}{/yonder, there's just ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.03,0:47:55.58,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is soft volcanic ash and lapilli.{あとは柔らかな火山灰と火山礫の層だ。}{/then, there's also a layer of soft/slushy volcanic soil and volcanic pebbles/gravel}
Dialogue: 0,0:47:55.58,0:48:00.96,Default,,0,0,0,,In addition, the road to that grazeland is in fine shape, \Nso transporting equipment would be optimal{/a walk in a park}!{それにあすこまでは牧場の道も立派にあるから、材料を運ぶことも造作ない。}{/besides, because there such a perfect road to that pasture, moving materials there won't pose a problem}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:00.96,0:48:02.65,Default,,0,0,0,,I will get it underway.{/I will arrange the works at once.}{ぼくは工作隊を申請しよう。}{/I'm going to muster/apply for/request a construction team/transport squad/an expedition}{kousaku is "construction/maneuvering/work" that I translated as "work" at 47:42 but here it's also "tai" which is a brigate/team so I'm not sure how to handle it; later I made it "construction battalion"}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.50,0:48:08.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Put me through to Director.{局長}{/connect me to ...}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:11.01,0:48:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, Pennen Nam speaking.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:13.30,0:48:15.10,Default,,0,0,0,,That's right, we have an emergency.{/the danger is imminent/urgent/immediate}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.31,0:48:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, gauges! \NConduct a check!{/instruments/machinery! Do a check!}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:19.02,0:48:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay...
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.52,0:48:21.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Hello? Yes!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:21.52,0:48:23.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Form{/organise/muster/send} a construction battalion{/again, "works team"} at once!
Dialogue: 0,0:48:23.44,0:48:25.56,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Then, I'm counting on you.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:27.32,0:48:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,The construction battalion is en route.{/the main office is sending out the working brigade at once}{局からすぐ工作隊を出すそうだ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:29.57,0:48:31.72,Default,,0,0,0,,I say "construction," \Nbut half the mean is "kamikaze."{/I say "construction [battalion]," \Nbut they are halfway "kamikaze."}{/it's nearly/halfly suicide squad}{工作隊といっても半分決死隊だ。}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:32.17,0:48:36.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Not yet once I had to do my job \Nin such proximity to the danger!{/Up until now, I have never had to work with hazard so imminent/so close to the danger}{私はいままでに、こんな危険に迫った仕事をしたことがない。}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:36.26,0:48:40.37,Default,,0,0,0,,It must be your first time \Nworking on a near exploding volcano{/volcano about to explode},{/an actual erupting volcano} isn't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:40.37,0:48:41.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Brace yourself.{/be prepared}{覚悟をしたまえ}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.54,0:48:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,The time to get truly terrified \Nhas yet to come.{本当に怖い目に遭うのはこれから}{/the actual scary part is really just beginning/we have yet to live through something really dreadful}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:45.13,0:48:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, get a grip on yourself!{/Budori, get yourself together.}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:48.88,0:48:51.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Can we really... make it in time{added}?
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.47,0:48:52.66,Default,,0,0,0,,{/We got to try!}We {\i1}have{\i0} to do it!{/We definitely can/must make sure to manage}{きっとできる。}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:53.08,0:48:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,Even in 10 days, if need be.{/we have no choice but to make it in 10 days}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:56.44,0:48:58.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Three days for the setup.{/Three days for installation.}{装置には三日、}{souchi is equipment; device; installation; apparatus​/stage setting​}
Dialogue: 0,0:48:58.10,0:49:01.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Pulling the power lines \Nfrom Sanmutori power plant...{サンムトリ市の発電所から、電線を引いてくるには五日かかるな。}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:02.27,0:49:03.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Maybe 5 days.{/Won't take more than 5 days/I wonder if we can make it in 5 days}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:03.52,0:49:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, either way, Budori, \Nwhy don't we boil ourselves a cup of tea first?{/let's pass one cup of tea each, shan't we?}{一つ茶をわかして飲もうではないか。}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.34,0:49:08.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:09.98,0:49:13.07,Default,,0,0,0,,After all, the scenery is still breathtaking.{あんまりいい景色だから。}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.58,0:49:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor Kubo!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:37.60,0:49:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor...
Dialogue: 0,0:49:39.31,0:49:42.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Stopped by for a cup of tea. \NGot some boiling?{お茶をよばれに来たよ。ゆれるかい。}{yurerukai is actually "wanna shake/is it shaking" but this reeks of pun, though I'm clueless as to which word, saying he alludes to 茹でる (yuderu) - to boil/to seethe seems like a bit of stretch, but I don't see any better options, plus, it wouldn't hurt to just write in whatever fits better, even if it's not exactly what the original joke was, or even if there was no joke and he just genuinely wonders if they are not troubled with the aftershocks; I came up with "have you got some boiling tea/have you boiled some?" and a response of "tea - not yet, the lava, though..."}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.60,0:49:45.17,Default,,0,0,0,,We don't yet have any. \NThe magma, though...{まだそんなでない。どうも岩が}{/nothing of the kind yet, but the rocks...}{original line is "まだそんなでない。どうも岩がぼろぼろ上から落ちているらしいんだ。"}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:46.48,0:49:47.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Pennen!
Dialogue: 0,0:49:48.11,0:49:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes!{/Let's go!}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:52.57,0:49:57.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it takes, we must finish \Nthe construction of tidal power plants next year!{もうどうしても、来年は潮汐発電所を全部作ってしまわなければならない。}{holy shit, barely anyone knew about tidal power in 1930 but this really is in the book}
Dialogue: 0,0:49:57.43,0:50:01.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Once we do, whenever something like this reoccurs, \Nwe can start working that same day.{それができれば今度のような場合にもその日のうちに仕事ができるし、}{/if we do that, in cases like that of today, we would have our electicity on-spot/won't have to rely on others/would be able to get to work within the day of occurence}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:01.45,0:50:05.36,Default,,0,0,0,,It will also allow for a widespread use \Nof Budori's suggested paddy fertilizer.{/ブドリ君が言っている沼畑の肥料も降らせられるんだ。}{/In addition, the paddy fertilizer (he actually uses another word than usual for fertilizer) that Budori is talking about - we would be able to make it rain/to shed it}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.36,0:50:06.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Drought would also be go—{/旱魃だってこわく[なくなるからな]。}{/even a drought will no longer be scary/a threat}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.67,0:50:09.29,Default,,0,0,0,,We'll do it, we will!{やるぞ、やるぞ。}{Might as well be "it's doing it/it really does/we really should [finish tidal plants/let's do it/etc"]}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.29,0:50:13.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now this one must be perceptible enough \Neven all the way down to Sanmutori!{いまのはサンムトリの市の方も、かなり感じたにちがいない。}{/I'm sure the people in the city of Sanmutori must have felt it quite a bit too.}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.88,0:50:19.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Just now, in about a kilometer north of our footing,{/from where we're standing with our feet} \Napproximately{he uses different words for "about/roughly/approximately" here} 700 meters deep into the earth{/[down] under the surface},
Dialogue: 0,0:50:19.82,0:50:24.79,Default,,0,0,0,,a chunk{/mass/cluster} of rocks, roughly 60-70{he says "six seventy times" which may be 60-70/6-70/x670} times this shack in size{he just says "x times this hut" but what else can it be}, \Nplunged hard{/fell down} into the lava!{/lodged itself under the fault(?)}{今のはぼくらの足もとから、北へ一キロばかり、地表の下七百メートルぐらいの所で、この小屋の六七十倍ぐらいの岩の塊が熔岩の中へ落ち込んだらしい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:29.36,0:50:30.31,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:30.31,0:50:32.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I shall thus have my leave.{そうだ、僕はこれで失敬しよう。}{/I'll leave you at that/if you excuse me, I'll be on my way}
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.90,0:50:33.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Professor?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:37.66,0:50:41.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, I look forward to seeing \Nhow you handle this assignment.{/job/I put high hopes on your manner of work}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:06.64,0:51:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here.{/Then,}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:08.22,0:51:09.61,Default,,0,0,0,,The rest is up to you.{/I entrust the rest to you}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.54,0:51:30.29,Default,,0,0,0,,Here they are, here they are!{/they come, they come} \NThe construction battalion.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:30.29,0:51:31.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, I'll be on my way, too.{/I should also start (start what? heck if I know)}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:31.58,0:51:32.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:35.42,0:51:37.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, now for a long way down.{/then, I'll descend/go down}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.46,0:51:40.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You stay here to manage and monitor \Nthe machines at all times.{引き続き機械の管理と観測を続けて}{/Budori, without a break/constantly, continue to control and observe the machinery/instruments/gauges(I used gauges before for that word, but you can't manage the gauge, I guess)}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:40.58,0:51:43.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep me informed of the situation{ here} \Nvia that phone.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:43.18,0:51:44.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang in there.{/Keep up the good work.}{/And do your best}
Dialogue: 0,0:51:44.43,0:51:45.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.84,0:52:01.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.40,0:52:02.99,Default,,0,0,0,,This was a strong one{ right now}.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:02.99,0:52:05.33,Default,,0,0,0,,You have the gas pressure and mounting rate{ [data]}?{atsuryoku is pretty simple but the second word is either "boujou/gojou/doujo" with the suffix either "ritsu" or "sa"; none of the words with that pronunciation qute fit the context, the closest one is 防除 as "protection (against natural disasters)"; suffixes, however are ritsu = rate/ratio and sa = -ness, so you can say I made this one up from just a suffix which I'm also only 50% sure of; in the book, it's "mountain shape"; rus sub says "density"}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:05.58,0:52:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:06.77,0:52:09.66,Default,,0,0,0,,There has not been a major change{/is no significant difference with the data} in comparison{/from before now}.{だいたい今までの時と大きくは変わってません}{/generally, it has not changed a lot from the time before now}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.66,0:52:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,I see.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:10.57,0:52:13.13,Default,,0,0,0,,{Over }Here, the seismic activity \Nis too strong to keep going.{/withstand}{Lit: on this end, the earthquake is heavy, cannot go; my best bet is こっちは地震動重いはに行かないよ, though omoi may mean "thoughts/memories" as well as "heavy/strong" and ikanai is "go/move" but not exactly "continue/carry on" so I'm unsure about those two}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:13.13,0:52:15.90,Default,,0,0,0,,But everyone is doing their best. \NThen, till later.{/we'll hear from each other again}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.93,0:52:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori? Budori!\NHey, report{/what's wrong}! Are you alright up there?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:42.33,0:52:43.99,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:52:45.91,0:52:46.99,Default,,0,0,0,,Report!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.99,0:52:48.79,Default,,0,0,0,,Something's wrong{/going on/happened}? \NAnswer me!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:48.79,0:52:49.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori!
Dialogue: 0,0:52:49.77,0:52:50.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hold on!{/keep yourself together}
Dialogue: 0,0:52:50.48,0:52:52.05,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm on my way,{/I will come now} don't give up!
Dialogue: 0,0:53:03.55,0:53:06.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri... Neri! Neri!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:06.30,0:55:06.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori!
Dialogue: 0,0:55:07.30,0:55:08.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Pennen?
Dialogue: 0,0:55:09.68,0:55:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You made it out in one piece...{/so you were alright after all}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:11.74,0:55:12.52,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.00,0:55:15.47,Default,,0,0,0,,But we only have 5 to 6 hours before Sanmutori erupts.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:16.98,0:55:19.60,Default,,0,0,0,,Before that, a smaller eruption will also occur.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:19.60,0:55:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,We have{ no choice but} to somehow finish it{/the rest} in just 4 hours.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:23.52,0:55:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,At least you are alright.{/anyway, I'm glad}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:24.88,0:55:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's hurry.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:37.19,0:55:39.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, please wake up. \NWe are starting{/it's on}.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:40.21,0:55:41.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Please wake up! We're starting.
