Dialogue: 5,0:55:43.32,0:55:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The power plant is on the line.{/phone connection to ... established}{unsure about that tsuji word but the rest is solid so this is kinda predefined, too}
Dialogue: 5,0:55:45.22,0:55:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright.
Dialogue: 5,0:55:46.29,0:55:47.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Commence the operation!{/begin at that, please}
Dialogue: 5,0:55:47.74,0:55:48.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:56.78,0:55:58.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Why the wait?{/what's the matter}
Dialogue: 0,0:55:59.14,0:56:00.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, redial them.{/give me the phone}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:01.60,0:56:02.68,Default,,0,0,0,,A moment, please.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:07.99,0:56:08.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's here.{/it starts}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:14.51,0:56:15.43,Default,,0,0,0,,That way!{/over there}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:31.48,0:56:34.43,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone, take cover in{/enter/hide in} tents! Now!{/hurry}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.43,0:56:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And you too, Budori!
Dialogue: 0,0:56:37.26,0:56:38.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thank you.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:38.87,0:56:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Quick!{/hurry}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:46.11,0:56:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Would that be enough?{/did we manage it}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:47.94,0:56:49.18,Default,,0,0,0,,It was a success.{/it worked/went well}
Dialogue: 0,0:56:56.71,0:57:03.17,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:56:59.89,0:57:01.06,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.87,0:57:05.89,Default,,0,0,0,,I checked with the{/made sure at the} Volcanology University.{not sure what he ascertained here, the timings the budori forecasted? the course of eruption, implying Budori was right when he said "not yet time to redial them" or something that happened while the camera was not shooting? would work under the timings option}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:05.89,0:57:09.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just as you said. \NEverything went exactly according to the plan{ after all}.{all according to keikaku ☜(ﾟヮﾟ☜)}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:09.65,0:57:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that so?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.34,0:57:12.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a relief...{/Glad to know}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:12.51,0:57:20.25,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.79,0:57:15.79,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:16.36,0:57:17.41,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:17.78,0:57:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:23.55,0:57:24.55,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:28.57,0:57:32.39,Default,,0,0,0,,At last, the plan for 200 tidal power plants \Nhas been carried out swimmingly{toutou may be 滔々 (torrentially; swiftly flowing (water, esp. river); voluminously flowing/flood/currents) as well as "finally" and I think this may be intended as a pun, maybe something like "the 200th tpp is now afloat" would work too}.{/finally, the 200th tidal pp is completed}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:32.39,0:57:34.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes, a new era is in sight.{/this is like a new era.}{literal "it's from now on, isn't it" (goddamnit pennen really has a fetish for korekara) makes no sense}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:34.71,0:57:37.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, much more is yet to be done.{/we should work even more from now on}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:37.62,0:57:41.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes. Today as well, \NBudori is running around volcanoes.{unsure if 走り回って is exactly that, may be "visiting" or "inspecting" as russub suggests}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:41.22,0:57:43.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What a diligent young man!{/young man is doing his very best}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:43.12,0:57:44.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, let's go with that.{/do it this way}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:53.47,0:57:56.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, it says{added} the fertilizer will be raining from the sky!
Dialogue: 0,0:57:56.74,0:57:58.49,Default,,0,0,0,,Like the usual rain?{/alike to the rain}
Dialogue: 0,0:57:58.49,0:57:59.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Preposterous! {/What a nonsense/that's silly}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:00.41,0:58:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Nitrogen fertilizer is being sprayed.{/it will rain ...}{窒素肥料を降らせます。}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.47,0:58:09.00,Default,,0,0,0,,This summer, along with the rain, the ammonium nitrate{I looked it up, this is the exact name of the fertilizer} \Nwill fall out{/precipitate} on everyone's rice paddies and vegetable plots.{ことしの夏、雨といっしょに、硝酸アムモニヤをみなさんの沼ばたけや蔬菜ばたけに降らせますから、}{/in summer this year, together with the rain, the nitric acid ammonia will be sprinkled over youy paddies and vegetable gardens}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:09.00,0:58:12.33,Default,,0,0,0,,If you already use fertilizer, \Nplease include this dose in your reckoning.{肥料を使うかたは、その分を入れて計算してください。}{/those using their own fertilizer, please redo your calculations with that number/share/amount/dose in mind/included/considered}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:12.82,0:58:16.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Planned dose is 120 kilograms \Nper 100 square meters.{分量は百メートル四方につき百二十グラムです。}{in the book, it's 120 kilograms, but here they either dropped or lost "kilo" and to anyone with a basic understanding of gardening, this number is ridiculously small. If we have to choose the lesser evil, do we assume nobody cares}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:17.01,0:58:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,It will also cause a bit more rains.{雨もすこしは降らせます。}{Lit is "rain, too, will rain a little/We will also let it rain a little" so I assumed they mean "we'll make the rain occur a bit more often" but suspecting "there will also be a little rain in that fertilizer"}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:19.06,0:58:24.80,Default,,0,0,0,,There'll be enough drop for the crops \Nto be irrigated even in case of drought.{/Even if a drought is impending, we'll be able to generate enough rain for the crops to sustain it nevertheless.}{旱魃の際には、とにかく作物の枯れないぐらいの雨は降らせることができますから、}{/in the event of a drought, enough rain will be sprinkled for the plants to not wilt/wither anyway, therefore...}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:24.80,0:58:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,If you have paddies left fallow \Ndue to concern about water,{/If there are as well paddies you abstained from cultivating due to lack of water until now,}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.04,0:58:30.81,Default,,0,0,0,,this year, sow these the heart light{/please use them for planting with easy heart}.{いままで水が来なくなって作付けしなかった沼ばたけも、ことしは心配せずに植え付けてください。}{/this year, please have no worries when planting seeds also in the paddies you did not use for seeding before, wary of the water not reaching them}{he uses two different words for "to plant" here: sakutzuke / uetsukete, the second is stronger and also means transplant/replant so maybe he means "spread your plants to those newly reclaimed paddies as well"?}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.81,0:58:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,- Ihatovo Volcanology University.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.42,0:58:36.62,Default,,0,0,0,,It's almost time.{/soon enough}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:52.48,0:58:53.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It's out!{/it came/started}
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.32,0:58:55.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And...{/alright,} now!
