Dialogue: 0,0:59:10.00,0:59:10.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect!{/good}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:11.17,0:59:12.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Perfect, that's the way.{/keep it up}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.97,0:59:27.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, down here, all's in order{/fine/everything is ready}.{下のほうはすっかりいい。}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:27.83,0:59:29.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It's pouring rain!{雨はざあざあ降っている。}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.75,0:59:31.48,Default,,0,0,0,,The airship has just returned.{船はいま帰って来た。}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.48,0:59:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,I think that's enough for now.{もうよかろうと思う。}{unsure, he may mean something like "I think it's safe to say already, this has been a success/all probably went very well"}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.08,0:59:34.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Commence the operation!{/start the procedure on your end, too}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:34.42,0:59:36.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:52.92,0:59:55.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Ammonium nitrate \Nis already being exuded{/sprayed} into the rain.{硝酸アムモニヤはもう雨の中へでている。}{Lit: ... is already out inside the rain/to mix with the rain}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:55.80,0:59:57.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The amount is also nigh perfect.{my best guess is 量もどんどんぐらいもいい - the quantity/volume is steadily approaching good, too/about good}
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.88,1:00:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Keep it going{/on} for another 4 hours or so!{あと四時間ほどつづけてやってくれたまえ。}{/keep doing it/continue for a span of about four more hours}
Dialogue: 0,1:00:00.63,1:00:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Roger.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:06.82,1:00:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Did it!{/hooraay}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:01.90,1:01:05.05,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Volcanology University — \Nthe new hope for agriculture!{/the new light of farming}{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:05.05,1:01:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you like that?{/ain't that cool}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:06.53,1:01:07.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Here, too.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.83,1:01:11.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}The breakthrough{added} idea, \Nsuggested by a young scholar{局員 is rather "clerk/employee"} Gusko Budori{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.08,1:01:15.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}and {with }Professor Kubo{'s assistance}, has been fearlessly{added} implemented{/realized/brought into life} \Nby Volcanology University staff!{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:17.25,1:01:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here. Once again, filled with thanks.{/another one mountain of gratutides - I hope he uses mountain as "heap/bunch" here}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:21.69,1:01:26.26,Default,,0,0,0,,That is the most solid proof of how everyone's hard work \Nbrought blessing upon countless people!{/this too, shows how thanks to everyone of you doing your best, that many people were made happy}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.26,1:01:29.14,Default,,0,0,0,,Still, what about the leading protagonist?{肝心の主役 - don't wanna use "hero" because it repeats 2 lines later, maybe "star of the day/key actor"?}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:31.27,1:01:36.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori said the Tachina{タチナ} volcano \Nis gnawing away at him{/giving him a hitch in the giddyup/reasons to worry}, so he went to examine{/observe/investigate} it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:36.15,1:01:38.24,Default,,0,0,0,,Naturally, as a hero of our ranks would!{/as expected from the hero of our university/bureau; the way he says it makes me think a double meaning is implied: waga sounds a bit like "young" and kyoku is a part of the word "clerk" used previously in the gazette; then again, it's only natural that "bureau clerk" has "bureau" in it}
Dialogue: 0,1:01:54.79,1:01:56.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Excuse me, don't you have any bread?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.85,1:01:59.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Bread we have, \Nbut it's not for people to eat that bread.{パンはあるが、どうも食われないパンでな。}{/it doesn't seem edible/it's not a bread you can bite/chew/eat/but no one eats that bread}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.31,1:02:02.34,Default,,0,0,0,,They mixed up "grain" with "gravel" for this one!{/wheat for grit}{石盤だものな。}{/just replace "ead" with "ick!"/rather, unbread-(k/c)able/You can pave the broad with it}{pun is "pun" being "bread" and "bun" being "a solid, hard sheet/plate/slab/plank", in this particular case - a stone slab; at the end of my wits, I couldn't think of a "cement" word similar to "bread" ¯\_(ツ)_/¯}{/With a gravel loaded extra!}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:05.34,1:02:09.50,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fs8\frx0\fry324\bord0\blur0.5\frz1.184\c&H000202&\3c&HA3CCB1&\pos(33.34,161.46)}Volcanology University
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.47,1:02:08.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey, you there!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.01,1:02:14.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Are you that Budori guy, \Nwho, with{/using} electricity, made fertilizer rain{/sprinkled ...} this summer?{ことしの夏、電気でこやし降らせたブドリだな。}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.74,1:02:15.75,Default,,0,0,0,,That is correct.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.10,1:02:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey! Budori from Volcanology University is here!{/has come}{火山局のブドリが来たぞ。みんな集まれ。}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:18.90,1:02:20.48,Default,,0,0,0,,What, did you say Budori?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:20.48,1:02:21.32,Default,,0,0,0,,For real?{/!}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:21.32,1:02:22.82,Default,,0,0,0,,The one from {Volcanology }University?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:23.54,1:02:24.74,Default,,0,0,0,,Son of a dog!{/you, bastard}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:24.74,1:02:29.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks to your darn electricity, \Nall of our rice wilted before it could mature{I want him to be more specific with the reason here: if he just says "the rice died" - anything could be the reason, but if he articulates the reason, it would sound more natural for budori to then confidently repulse his allegation as some familiar to him result of too much NH4NO3}{/bought the farm of its own/dropped dead}!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.07,1:02:30.16,Default,,0,0,0,,Wilted prematurely?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.62,1:02:33.25,Default,,0,0,0,,But haven't you seen the posters \Nwe put out at spring?{春に出したポスターを見なかったのか。}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.25,1:02:35.62,Default,,0,0,0,,A son of a dog, and a noisy mouth at that!{/shut up, you bastard}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.29,1:02:37.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Wait!
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.61,1:02:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:47.05,1:02:48.08,Default,,0,0,0,,{What is }This place...{/here...?}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:55.65,1:02:56.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes?{/come in}
Dialogue: 0,1:02:57.60,1:02:58.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Pennen?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:00.27,1:03:02.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Recovering by leaps and bounds, are you?{changed to add consistency with Budori replying "yes" next}{/You look livelier than I expected/You look better than I thought you would}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:02.05,1:03:05.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, but I'm still clueless as to what and why{[happened there]}...{sappari is also "feeling refreshed/relieved" so it may be "somehow, somewhy, I'm feelinsh perked up" as well as "but I still have no idea what had happened"}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.01,1:03:07.31,Default,,0,0,0,,That was a bit of a fiasco.{sainan is "calamity; misfortune; disaster"; russub suggests "misunderstanding" which may work as well I reckon}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:07.31,1:03:10.70,Default,,0,0,0,,The village mayor{/headman/elder} has already brought \Nhis {hurried }apologies to the {Volcanology }University.{/came to the VU to ask for forgiveness in panic}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:11.12,1:03:13.87,Default,,0,0,0,,But what really happened \Nto the rice in that village?{/why did the rice fail ...}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:13.87,1:03:19.83,Default,,0,0,0,,About that, the village's main agronomist{/agricultural technician/engineer} \Nmade a blunder{added} and mishandled fertilizer use.{/instructed the misuse of fertilizer}{he really says "taught the completely wrong way to put in the fertilizer" but well, how can you fuck up applying the fertilizer? like, what other way is there to put it in?; this also may be "the wrong kind of fertilizer" or smth}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:20.25,1:03:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Then he thought it convenient to put the blame on you, \Nso praised by the newspapers.{/so he decided to deceive everyone by saying it was your fault, seeing how you are so famous/acclaimed in/all over newspapers}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.80,1:03:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Can you believe that?{/disgraceful, isn't it}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:26.34,1:03:27.28,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's it?{/is that so/so trifling}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:30.84,1:03:33.08,Default,,0,0,0,,You injuries are still fresh, you know?{/wounds have not healed yet}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:33.31,1:03:33.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:37.39,1:03:41.05,Default,,0,0,0,,But there is, actually, one more \Nvery special{/important} visitor you got.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.40,1:03:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So I'll leave you at that.{/have my leave}
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.32,1:03:45.35,Default,,0,0,0,,{\i1}Special?{\i0}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:03.54,1:04:04.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, but...{/you}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:18.85,1:04:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, your hat...
Dialogue: 0,1:04:27.23,1:04:29.40,Default,,0,0,0,,Sorry, can I help you?{/what's your business}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:42.64,1:04:43.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.05,1:04:51.20,Default,,0,0,0,,You really are...{/But how can that be}
Dialogue: 0,1:04:54.54,1:04:55.18,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:56.64,1:04:57.72,Default,,0,0,0,,But how{/why}?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.72,1:05:00.37,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, I got married.{it's a bit out of blue to just say that after the meeting, so I'm trying to make it more consequent, implying him asking "but how come you changed that much" and her replying "you see, I've been through a lot, even got married"}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:00.37,1:05:01.28,Default,,0,0,0,,I see...
Dialogue: 0,1:05:01.64,1:05:04.73,Default,,0,0,0,,My husband{this is tricky, because "shujin" may be "master/owner of the farm/landlord"} was listening to morning news,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:05.65,1:05:06.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and then...{my best bet for this line is 聞いて, but you can't exactly "hear" the newspaper, so I'm implying he either heard it on radio or while some other folks were discussing the news, although "... read about you in this morning's newspaper" as russub suggests would work as well}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:08.90,1:05:10.65,Default,,0,0,0,,But then, that man has{[let you go]}...{/but what about that man}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:11.44,1:05:12.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Yes.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.53,1:05:17.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Since then, I have been crying all the time.{/I kept crying without a break}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.34,1:05:18.74,Default,,0,0,0,,He could no longer bear it,{手を焼 - had difficulty with me/I became too troublesome/too much of a hassle/gave him a hard time/was embarassing him}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:19.16,1:05:24.73,Default,,0,0,0,,so after 2 or 3 days of carrying{to be fair, I'm not sure what verb is "tsuru" here} me, \Nhe dropped me near a small ranch{before, I translated this word as pasture; here, though, it is later used to refer to the whole complex of facilities} and fled.{/he left me in the vicinity of a small grazing land and went elsewhere}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:25.82,1:05:28.21,Default,,0,0,0,,There, the ranch owner{again, shujin, though here it's clearly not husband} found me.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.21,1:05:31.13,Default,,0,0,0,,He took pity on me and let me into the house.{/felt sorry for me so he took me home}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:31.13,1:05:33.53,Default,,0,0,0,,There, they let me babysit and do the housework.{/they tasked me with looking after their children and working on the ranch}{although unlikely, I'm not etirely sure "komori" is not self-reflexive verb and is not implying "the looked after me while I was a child"}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.30,1:05:40.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Eventually, there was not a single job on the ranch \Nthat I haven't mastered.{/before long, I could do about every single kind of ranch work there is}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:40.39,1:05:44.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, 3 or{/to} 4 years ago, \NI married the eldest of their sons.{lit is "the eldest son of that place"}{そこのいちばん上の息子と結婚したのです。}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:44.79,1:05:47.91,Default,,0,0,0,,As for now, we also have a son.{/now, we already have one son}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:47.91,1:05:53.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Ours was a measly homestead{/poor ranch/small farm}, but this year, \Nthe fertilizer was{ also} raining, so we had a record yield of maize.{/the corn was doing extremely well/the output of corn was great}{/We are poor, but this year, thanks to the fertilizer rain, we had a record yield of corn.}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.20,1:05:56.71,Default,,0,0,0,,The ranch was faring well again, \Nand we were all over the moon with it.{/the homestead was afloat, too, so this made everyone in our household/family/home extremely happy}
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.71,1:06:00.73,Default,,0,0,0,,All this time, we were so busy with work, \Nwe barely had any time to read newspapers.{/we were always so preoccupied, we hardly ever been able to read newspapers properly}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:04.75,1:06:06.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Sounds as you've had hard times{/like you had one hell of a time}.{this feels stylistically off, but I'm out of ideas}{/it was very difficult, wasn't it?}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:07.13,1:06:11.34,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you did.{/it was you who did/it was much harder for you} \NYet you achieved such heights nevertheless.{/but now, look at what a magnificient work you've done/your dazzling achievements}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:11.71,1:06:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It's nothing, I'm just an apprentice.{/not yet time to claim that, I'm still just learning}{my bet is 見習いだよ}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.01,1:06:14.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Brother!
Dialogue: 0,1:06:15.72,1:06:16.63,Default,,0,0,0,,I was...
Dialogue: 0,1:06:17.08,1:06:19.81,Default,,0,0,0,,I was sure, I am now all alone{一人ぼっち} in this world!{/I thought I had become the loneliest being to ever survive}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:20.26,1:06:21.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So I married.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.47,1:06:25.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Yet I kept looking for brother, \Nwith whom our separation was so gust-like{the word's another meaning is "wind" so I'm improvising}...{Lit: but about my brother, with whom I was separated in that [forceful/violent] manner, I always [kept looking for him]/I never forgot about him/yet I always knew, my brother ... [was alive] - I can only guess here}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:26.10,1:06:28.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Neri, I feel you, but there's no need.{/I understand [your feelings], but [look at that/think yourself]}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:29.11,1:06:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We are hereafter reunited.{/from now on, we are together [again]}
Dialogue: 0,1:06:30.97,1:06:31.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Right, Neri?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:36.40,1:06:40.16,Sign,,0,0,0,,{\fad(10,0)\fs11\c&H0C1815&\3c&H7E9694&\bord0.5\blur1\pos(265.56,143.93)}Woodcutter \Nand his wife {yeah, it is tomb - 墓}                \h
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.84,1:07:44.12,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the matter? \NBudori, you look panic-stricken{/'re like a hurricane}.{https://jisho.org/word/%E6%85%8C%E3%81%A6%E3%82%8B - may be both "confused/disorganized" and "in a hurry"}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.10,1:07:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.52,1:07:48.23,Default,,0,0,0,,Meteorological survey report:{/I heard about that at weather measurement station (測候所)}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:48.57,1:07:54.55,Default,,0,0,0,,If you look at the sun's condition and the... \NAnd the ice observation data in the northernmost regions...{/Judging by the condition of the sun and the north... The glaciers in the north observation data, I looked at it and...}
Dialogue: 0,1:07:54.55,1:07:57.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori, I know exactly what you're trying to say{/understand ... want to convey}.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:57.28,1:08:01.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Moreover, Professor Kubo is already losing his sleep \Ntrying to come up with a solution.{/is also exhausting his wits/doing his best/trying all sorts of various things to help you/to find a way around it}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.18,1:08:01.91,Default,,0,0,0,,Then!...
Dialogue: 0,1:08:01.91,1:08:06.52,Default,,0,0,0,,It is expected,{/Unsurprisingly,} a once-in-decade severe famine \Nwill hit Ihatovo this year.{/a crop shortage, considered to be a once per ten years calamity in magnitude, will attack Ihatovo next year - rainen is actually next year, but they have a buttfuck in regards to "this/last/next year" in Japanese, so I would assume it's february now and they actually mean this year, because that's how it is in the book}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:07.28,1:08:08.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Knew it.{/[so it comes,] after all}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:08.74,1:08:10.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Then, what do we do about it?{/how should we act}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:11.46,1:08:12.88,Default,,0,0,0,,I have told you this once:{/same as I said before}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:14.00,1:08:19.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Since it's the nature itself we're struggling with, \Nit's always one step forward, two steps back.{/if the opponent/counterpart is the very force of nature, we can do naught/have no choice, but to make careful progress one step at a time/devise a way to move forward, one by one/keep having to come up with new ideas every step of the way}{/Since we contend against the forces of nature, it's always one step forward, two steps back.}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:27.10,1:08:32.48,Default,,0,0,0,,This cold season will extend into spring, \Nand summer is also expected to be colder than usual.{/the coldness will last/continue till spring, and the summertime is also going to become a cold summer (冷夏), we believe}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.48,1:08:34.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Farmers are advised to take caution.{/Those employed in agriculture, please be careful}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:34.77,1:08:35.98,Default,,0,0,0,,- Meteorological survey.{sokkoujo again}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:35.98,1:08:37.37,Default,,0,0,0,,What's the meaning of this?{/what even is this}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:37.37,1:08:39.34,Default,,0,0,0,,The crop{凶作} is going to be poor again!{/it'll be another one period of bad harvest}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:39.61,1:08:41.15,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?{/'s the best course of action}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:43.62,1:08:47.37,Default,,0,0,0,,{/At the present rate,}If no measures are taken, \Nthat famine will rear its head again.{/it'll bring about that detrimental famine again./if this keeps up, it'll become just like during that [last] famine}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:47.87,1:08:51.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Neither Professor Kubo, nor Volcanology University, \Nhave the power to avert it.{/both prof. kubo and volc. uni can't find a way to help it (im still unsure about uchite part but it must be some kind of "help/change/have a say in/alter")}
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.36,1:08:53.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What should I do?{/which would be good to do?}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:15.68,1:09:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!{/professor/sensei - I actually suggest this one, since the story is deeply rooted in japan}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.98,1:09:17.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Master!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.25,1:09:25.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Budori? What brings you here in the dead of night? \NAnd without any cover at that!{/why are you here in the middle of the night/so late into night? moreover, not holding an umbrella (https://www.lingq.com/en/learn-japanese-online/translate/ja/9931425/%E3%81%95%E3%81%95-%E3%81%9A/)}{/And dressed less warmly!}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:24.00,1:09:25.60,Default,,0,0,0,,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:25.60,1:09:27.58,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, please hear me out!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:27.58,1:09:31.44,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm sorry for bothering you at such an hour, \Nbut the matter is most urgent!{/I feel really bad for waking you up at a time like this, but this cannot wait, at all.}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.66,1:09:35.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Regardless, you should first come in and warm yourself.{/either way, hurry up inside to get warmed}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:36.63,1:09:37.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Thanks for your trouble{added}!
Dialogue: 0,1:09:42.51,1:09:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Master...
Dialogue: 0,1:09:43.09,1:09:44.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang that thing{/put it away} and have some tea.{/Help yourself to the tea first}{kakete may be "pour" (like, "drink what has been poured for you") or "hang [that coat]" but both seem a stretch although later the "hang" meaning is confirmed, plus, kakeru is a billion of other things as well}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.88,1:09:46.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's about the Carbonado Volcano.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:46.59,1:09:50.65,Default,,0,0,0,,A volcano detonation of this scale \Nwould massively release carbon dioxide gas!{technically, 炭酸ガス is "carbonic acid gas", however, there is no such thing, because carbonic acid is a liquid solution, the carbon dioxide is close enough, also that'd make perfect sense science-wise, this sums it up: http://www.cev.washington.edu/story/Ocean_Acidification_Illustrations.html}{/if this volcano erupts/explodes now at this scale, it'll emit/let out carbonic acid gas}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:50.65,1:09:54.31,Default,,0,0,0,,Hang that now! \NAnd then enjoy your tea {\i1}thoroughly{\i0}.{/drink all of your tea}
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.80,1:10:04.54,Default,,0,0,0,,Master, if the carbon dioxide gas concentration rises \Nin the stratosphere{lit is "in the air layer" which I don't quite grasp, because there's a separate word for "atmosphere" in JP, so I figured it may be one the the atmosphere layers (and if so, why not the biggest one and most probable), because up to now I have been trying to be more scientifically specific in budori's lines (he's a scholar, after all!) and if it's not "stratosphere" or not any "-sphere" at all - no big deal}, the climate will get warmer, won't it?{先生、気層のなかに炭酸ガスがふえれば、気候は暖かくなるのですか。}{/if carbonic acid increases in the atmosphere, ...}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:04.86,1:10:06.37,Default,,0,0,0,,That is quite possible.{それはなるだろう。}{/that's the way it works}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:08.47,1:10:11.79,Default,,0,0,0,,The commonly favored theory is, \Never since the earth formed,{/The generally accepted concept is, ever since the earth formed,}
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.87,1:10:17.08,Default,,0,0,0,,carbon dioxide gas concentration in the atmosphere \Nis determinant in its global temperature.{/has been determining its temperature.}{地球ができてからいままでの気温は、たいてい空気中の炭酸ガスの量できまったと言われるくらいだからね。}{/from the moment the earth was created and to this day, its temperature was majorly/mostly decided/adjusted by the amount of co2 in the air - that's what I'm told/they say}
